  "text": "The CODEOWNERS infrastructure in grafana/grafana consists of five main components:\n\n1. **CODEOWNERS File** (.github/CODEOWNERS): The GitHub ownership definition that maps repository paths to owning teams and users, establishing code ownership across the repository.\n\n2. **CI Validation Workflow** (.github/workflows/codeowners-validator.yml): Automated workflow that validates the CODEOWNERS file using the mszostok/codeowners-validator action, checking for syntax errors, duplicate patterns, and unowned files on pull requests.\n\n3. **Manifest Generation Scripts** (scripts/codeowners-manifest/): A JavaScript toolchain for parsing and indexing CODEOWNERS data:\n   - index.js: Main entry point orchestrating the complete manifest generation with caching\n   - generate.js: Generates manifest files (teams.json, teams-by-filename.json, filenames-by-team.json) from raw audit data\n   - raw.js: Generates raw audit JSONL using the github-codeowners CLI tool\n   - metadata.js: Generates metadata.json with file and CODEOWNERS hashes for cache validation\n   - constants.js: Defines paths for all manifest files\n\n4. **Go Type Definition** (pkg/services/featuremgmt/codeowners.go): Defines the codeowner type as a string alias with constants for all Grafana teams (@grafana/...). The FeatureFlag struct in models.go uses this type in the Owner field to assign ownership of feature flags.\n\n5. **Feature Management Integration** (pkg/services/featuremgmt/):\n   - models.go: FeatureFlag struct with codeowner Owner field\n   - registry.go: Feature flag definitions using codeowner constants\n   - feature_toggle_api/types.go: Feature and FeatureSpec types with codeowner field\n\n6. **Test Coverage Tooling**:\n   - jest.config.codeowner.js: Jest configuration for running tests scoped to files owned by specific teams\n   - scripts/test-coverage-by-codeowner.js: Orchestrates test coverage collection by team ownership\n\n7. **npm Scripts** (package.json): Orchestrates manifest generation:\n   - codeowners-manifest: Main command\n   - codeowners-manifest:clean: Cleans manifest directory\n   - codeowners-manifest:generate: Generates processed manifests\n   - codeowners-manifest:metadata: Generates metadata\n   - codeowners-manifest:raw: Generates raw audit data\n   - test:coverage:by-codeowner: Runs test coverage for specific teams\n\nThe infrastructure enables feature flag ownership tracking, team-based test coverage analysis, and automated CODEOWNERS validation throughout the development workflow."
}

